                     THe laws of Englad, in those thīgs, which they by force of the Law of nature do ratifie &amp; establish, are neither better nor worse in their iudgements, then the lawes of all other nations are in ye like cases. For as Aristotle in the 5. booke of his Morall Philosophie saith: The Law of nature is that which among all people

hath like strength and power, wherefore hereof to reason any longer it shall not auaile. But now henceforth we will search out what manner of Customes &amp; Statutes these of England are. And first the quallitie of those customes wee will consider.
                  
               
               
